The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bihar in AirTel loop

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Bharti Enterprises chairman and group managing director Sunil Mittal (left) in Patna on Monday at the launch of AirTel services in Bihar. (PTI)

 Patna, Jan. 17: AirTel today launched mobile services in Bihar, taking the number of circles it straddles to 21. It is the third cell firm in the state, after Bharat Sanchar Nigam and Reliance.

 ?AirTel will reach 1200 kilometres of highways, key rail routes and over 100 towns. It will be supported by a robust network of 150 cell sites that will facilitate innovative value-added services to customers,? said a release from Bharti, the firm that owns the AirTel brand. 

 The firm has launched a New Year AirTel bonanza. Innovative services like Airtel Live and Hello Tunes with popular Bhojpuri songs are key features of the plan. ?Telecom catalyses growth of the economy. Bihar has huge potential for improvement in telecom penetration. AirTel?s launch will go a long way in establishing this objective,? Bharti chief Sunil Mittal said.




